# Release and share

Package and publish outputs so others can find, trust, and reuse them — and so nothing sensitive or unverified leaves by accident. Get the checks done before anything goes out the door.

Verify before you publish. Complete the `docs/checklists/data-bulletproofing-checklist.md` so the numbers reconcile against the source's own totals and surprising results have been double-checked, and run the `docs/checklists/data-quality-checklist.md` where the data warrants it. Reconciliation against originals is what makes a dataset defensible; shipping unverified figures is how a project loses its credibility in one release.

Package in open, version-stamped formats with a defined export. Release processed outputs in plain-text, version-controllable formats (CSV/Parquet, Markdown, text-based pipeline definitions), stamp each release with a version and date, and provide a defined, scriptable export rather than a hand-assembled snapshot. The shared artifact is the re-runnable pipeline, not a one-off cleaned file: anything a hosted tool produces must be exportable, and no vendor-locked artifact should be a required dependency. Ship the `DATA-DICTIONARY.md` (and the Data Card, where you maintain one) alongside the data so a reader can interpret it.

Apply the access tier and respect the escalation rules. Before publishing, apply the access tier from `docs/governance/GOVERNANCE.md` — decide what is public, what is restricted, and who may touch which traces — and confirm the openness and license you are releasing under (`{{OPENNESS}}`, `{{LICENSE}}`).

<!-- IF:DATAVERSE -->Deposit for a citable archive. To make the release findable and citable, deposit the processed data, code, and documentation in a Dataverse repository for a DOI — see `dataverse/DEPOSIT.md`. Try a `DRY_RUN=1` deposit against `demo.dataverse.org` first; the deposit creates a reviewable draft and only publishes (mints the DOI) on explicit confirmation, after the bulletproofing and — where data is sensitive — responsible-data checks pass.<!-- /IF -->

<!-- IF:OPENSHARING -->Share in place, zero-copy. To give partners working access without handing over a copy, share the processed tables, file/doc volumes, and the project's `.skills/` via OpenSharing — see `opensharing/SHARING.md`. Decide what enters the share with the `docs/governance/GOVERNANCE.md` access tiers (scope the recipient, desensitize, or withhold), serve it from your object storage behind a sharing server, and keep the recipient bearer token out of the repo.<!-- /IF -->

<!-- IF:SENSITIVE -->This project handles **{{SENSITIVITY_TIER}}** data. Nothing touching sensitive traces is published on your own authority: route it through the access tiers and the remedy/escalation rules in `docs/governance/GOVERNANCE.md` first, desensitize before anything leaves the controlled tier, and complete the `docs/checklists/responsible-data-checklist.md`. Identifiers and retained data carry duties — releasing an affordance without its governance is exactly the theater this project refuses to ship.<!-- /IF -->
